# NAVYK Database Rules

## Principles
- Every table: id (uuid), createdAt, updatedAt
- Soft delete: deletedAt, isActive for main entities
- All enums in Prisma schema as enum types
- Explicit FK with named relations
- Text fields with potential search: add index

## Naming
- Tables: snake_case, plural (users, opportunities)
- Fields: camelCase in Prisma schema (firstName, createdAt)
- Indexes: idx_table_field
- FK: table_id pattern (userId, opportunityId)

## Forbidden
- SELECT * in production code
- Transactions longer than 5 seconds
- Storing passwords/tokens in plaintext
- Storing files in DB (S3 URLs only)
